*steps to reproduce*
- disable all build agents
- start a couple of builds and see that they're queued via the UI
- run {{curl -X GET --user USERNAME "BAMBOO_ADDRESS/rest/api/latest/queue?max-results=100"}}
- see that it returns something similar to:
{code:xml}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?><queue expand="queuedBuilds"><link href="http://localhost:8085/rest/api/latest/queue" rel="self"/><queuedBuilds start-index="0" max-result="1" size="1"/></queue>
{code}
which doesn't provide any details on the builds in the queue

The documentation for this endpoint is quoted as:
{quote}
enforce executing all stages in a plan, even if defined as manual stages. Execution will follow and include latest stage, unless some stage will fail.
{quote}

Hitting the endpoint does not however fire off manual stages.

*Steps to reproduce*
- Create a job with two stages and simple script tasks
- Set the second stage to be a manual run
- Run {{curl -X POST --user USERNAME "BAMBOO_SERVER_ADDRESS/rest/api/latest/queue/FOO-BAR1?executeAllStages=true"}}
- See that only the non-manual stage is appropriately fired off

