	{"Administrator": ["View","Edit","Build","Clone","Admin"]},
	{"MyUser": ["View","Build"]}
]
}
{code}

When a merge commit message from a pull request is displayed in Bamboo, the pull request number should link to the pull request in Stash. For example, Stash will use the following commit message for the merge:

{code}Merge pull request #1234 in <REPO> from <BRANCH> to <BRANCH>...{code}

The #1234 part of the commit message should link to the appropriate pull request inside of Stash. This should work in a similar way that the JIRA issue key is linked back to JIRA.

Please, upgrade documentation [Configuring elastic instances to use the EBS|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Configuring+elastic+instances+to+use+the+EBS] as the same does not reflect current Bamboo UI.
!bamboo.elasticImageConfiguration.png|thumbnail!

{code:java}
package com.atlassian.bamboo.agent.elastic.server;

class RemoteElasticInstanceEbsHelperImpl implements RemoteElasticInstanceEbsHelper
{
...
    private void createEbsVolumes(final RemoteEC2Instance ec2Instance, @NotNull final Collection<Pair<String, Boolean>> volumes)
    {
        final InstanceStatus instanceStatus = ec2Instance.getInstanceStatus();
        final String snapshotOrVolumeId = elasticImageConfiguration.getEbsSnapshotId();
        if (snapshotOrVolumeId == null)
        {
            return;
        }

        final String volumeId;
        final boolean deleteOnTermination;
        if (isSnapshot(snapshotOrVolumeId))
        {
            volumeId = awsAccount.createVolume(snapshotOrVolumeId, instanceStatus.getAvailabilityZone());
            deleteOnTermination = true;
            log.info("Created volume " + volumeId + " for " + instanceStatus.getInstanceId());
        }
        else
        {
            volumeId = snapshotOrVolumeId;
            deleteOnTermination = false;
        }
        volumes.add(Pair.pair(volumeId, deleteOnTermination));
    }
...
}
{code}
If specifying a volume created out of snapshot in the "{{EBS volume / snapshot id}}" input field, the same will be deleted once the instance is terminated. However, by providing a volume in there, the same will be kept.

Please, provide "{{Use legacy EBS handling}}" reference to documentation.

*Problem:*
Running Bamboo v5.4.3 and [Cucumber Report Plugin|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.hindsighttesting.behave.cucumber-bamboo-plugin] v1.1.1 might cause {{java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space}} errors in Bamboo.

*Root cause:*
In some cases the results from the DB are padded:
{noformat}
2015-04-08 13:23:35,859 INFO [AtlassianEvent::0-BAM::EVENTS:pool-3-thread-11] [TestClassImpl] set: [ajsdlkj asjdlkasjdlk asjdlkjaslkd














                                   ]
{noformat}
This increases the memory requirements by two orders of magnitude in case of test processing.
A single build plan might have a large number of tests.
When saving results in the database, we must avoid those paddings in Bamboo.
The 1.1.1 version of the Cucumber plugin has a bug that adds white space to the end of test class names in the XML test results file on local developer machines, as well as Bamboo.

*Workaround:*
Run the following SQL query:
{code:sql}
update TEST_CLASS set TEST_CLASS_NAME = RTRIM(TEST_CLASS_NAME);
{code}

*Solution:*
Upgrade the plugin to 1.2.x version.
